1829500.caption: About
1829500.introHtml:
about 

Antoni Mestre was born on October 14, 1999 in Valencia.
He is a student of the degree in Computer Science at the Polytechnic University of Valencia, the degree in Applied Data Science at Open University of Catalonia and the diploma in International Law at United Nations Institute for Research.

At the age of 20, when he was in the third year of his degree, Antoni obtained a research grant at the Research Center on Software Production Methods, part of the Valencia Research Institute for Artificial Intelligence. His research interests include Human Centered AI, Explainable AI, Human Computer Interaction and Computational Neuroscience.

He is currently doing an internship at the United Nations. His work is developed in the Department of Safeguards and consists of the application of state-of-the-art AI and Data Science techniques to satellite imagery and open source information to support the mission of United Nations in the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons.
